3.2.1 Principle of MADM

For Network Selection, classical MADM approach consists in choosing the best network from available networks considering multiple attributes. The vertical handover decision problem can be formulated as a matrix form Q, where each row i corresponds to the candidate network and each column j corresponds to an attribute. The matrix of N alternative networks is settled conforming to M attributes.

