3.2.3.4 VIseKriterijumska Optimizacija I Kompromisno Resenje: VIKOR
The VlseKriterijumska Optimizacija I Kompromisno Resenje ”(VIKOR; that means multi-criteria optimization and compromise solution)”. It was elaborated for multi-criteria optimization of intricate systems Opricovic (1998) and Tzeng and Huang (2011). VIKOR is based on listing and choosing from a batch of available networks in consideration of an inconsistent metrics. It proposes the multi-criteria ranking key based on the speciﬁc measure of ”closeness” to the ”ideal” solution. The concept of VIKOR is hinged on ﬁguring out the compromise solution from ranking the alternatives regarding the weight coherence intervals which depend on the preference of the compromise solution provided with the original weights. The following steps are mandatory for VIKOR:

